channel.title: CVE Feed for IBM -- Security Verify Governance, Identity Manager
channel.description: The latest CVEs for IBM -- Security Verify Governance, Identity Manager

item.title: CVE-2023-35019|2024-08-02T16:17:04.347Z -- ibm -- security%20verify%20governance%2C%20identity%20manager
item.description: IBM Security Verify Governance, Identity Manager 10.0 could allow a remote authenticated attacker to execute arbitrary commands on the system by sending a specially crafted request. IBM X-Force ID: 257873.

item.title: CVE-2023-35016|2024-08-02T16:17:04.315Z -- ibm -- security%20verify%20governance%2C%20identity%20manager
item.description: IBM Security Verify Governance, Identity Manager 10.0 could allow a remote attacker to traverse directories on the system. An attacker could send a specially crafted URL request containing "dot dot" sequences (/../) to view arbitrary files on the system. IBM X-Force ID: 257772.
